text: Don’t EVER use this real estate company! Dawn Elder is the absolute WORST! She is VERY unprofessional and pursued my fiancé, calling him and having very “unethical” and “unprofessional” phone calls that were not related to our rental property AT ALL and then allowed him to start having “sleep overs” until she had him move in her house that she got in her divorce. She’s a liar and a terrible and untrustworthy person. I bought this lady flowers and a card when I rented this house from her because I thought she was a woman who had been through the same things I had been through and she seemed hurt by her ex husband as I was by mine, only to find out she was trying to do the SAME THING to ME the whole entire time with my fiancé! I rented this house through her in April and the key box lock on the back door is still on the door! The rooftops on both storage buildings were covered in pine straw and limbs that she had said would be cleaned along with the yard and they never were. Things weren’t fixed or painted as she claimed they’d be before we moved in and she said later they’d be done upon us moving in. Well that never happened either. Save yourself and your family the drama and the dissatisfaction and go to another realtor or definitely ask for anyone but DAWN ELDER!!!! Mrs Carol would have handled this lady appropriately if she was still alive and fired her home wrecking self!!

name: Charlie Herron
text: Trailers dilapidated and in various stages of collapse. I nearly froze to death in the winter. Rent is cheap but that's relative when you get a 400 dollar power bill.

resp.text:
Mr. Herron, All of our homes have fully functional ELECTRIC central heat. And the unit in your home was quite new. If you had issues during residency reports should have been made. Were any reports made to the office of ANY needed repairs? Upon report of needed repairs our full time maintenance person(s) take care of our homes. Upon leaving our community we found the unreported needs in the home where you resided,  they were addressed and we have had 2 very happy residents in that home in the time since you left including currently.

In our lease we ask for needed repairs to be reported timely. We prefer to take care of issues as they arise and never allow them to accumulate or become unkempt housing conditions. Believe me it costs us less to fix things as they become an issue and there is a great expense upon turnover to  bring one back from resident neglect. Had maintenance needs been reported both parties would have had a better experience during tenancy as well as had a better taste in each of our mouths at the end of residency.

I hope you have found happiness in your housing, since. Best wishes to you Mr. Herron.

resp.text:
We have a variety of homes including, those at well below market price to serve 1 st time renters and those just starting out. Most of our residents choose to upgrade to larger and more expensive homes as they have established a rental history and as their lives allow them to allocate more to rent. The smaller, older homes, as  are all of our homes are maintained by a full time maintenance person(s) and we fix things when they are reported and it is a reasonable request. There is a market in our community for homes under $500 and I am proud to say we offer the best around in that price point.

Have you ever taken a tour with me or applied to live in our community?

Yes we are indeed no dogs, since 2009. However we have a large number of residents who have lived here for 10+, 20+ and 30+ years. So you will see some residents with pets.

I appreciate the opportunity to clarify. Thank you for leaving a review.

name: jae eun myung
text:
2 hour driving range.  We researched many of the lakes in GA and nearby states.  One of the lakes in Alabama was Weiss Lake (roughly the same size as Lake Lanier).  Tyrone Miller was advertised online as an expert on Weiss Lake real estate and had several good reviews.  We contacted him on a Friday morning asking if he could arrange cabin tours around Weiss Lake on Saturday (yes, one day later!).  He agreed, asked a series of questions around the type of property we were looking for and developed a large list of properties that fit our needs exactly.  We met him the following morning and he spend most of the day with us reviewing several properties.  His translation from our brief discussion to the types of properties he showed us was absolutely perfect.

During our tour day, he continued adding homes to the list including contacting other realtors and owners that day asking for time to show us properties.   Finally he made one last minute appointment that he had been working on all day.  We saw the property, fell in love and decided then and there to make an offer.  There was no way this would have been possible without Tyrone.

First, Tyrone knows this area and people there very very well, so he could show us many options and manage our ridiculously tight schedule. Second, he was very honest about questions we asked about the various properties, value, water depth, comparisons to other properties he had sold, and price . Third, he is very punctual and efficient.  Even through the obstacles of our our distance, crazy schedule, and our very specific needs, Tyrone made us feel part of the community throughout the process.  Everything from the initial contact through the closing went very very smooth!

We are still getting great help from him as he is very willing to assist with local experts and advice even after our purchase.

If you want to find nice lakefront house or property and do it with the most professional and knowledgeable realtor in the area, Tyrone is the person to contact.

Thank you very much Tyrone!

text: Where do I begin? I recently transitioned from out of state to the Huntsville area. I knew about my relocation about 4 months before leaving my home and decided to get into contact with a realtor to get the ball rolling. I called about 4 or 5 different realtors before I got ahold of Liz Smith at Century21. She made our process smooth and efficient. Liz took the time to cater to all of our needs and wants. Over the course of our move she corresponded with us by email, over the phone and in person once we reached our destination. The time and commitment she took was paramount to our success. I believe she really takes all aspects of her clients situation into account and really makes it work in their favor with her ability to knock down walls and build bridges to achieve the desired outcome. I will definitely recommend Century21 Steele & Associates (Liz Smith) to anyone looking to rent/buy any real estate in the greater Huntsville area.
